<p>A jar contains <m>$d</m> ping pong balls, <m>$a</m> of which are blue and <m>$b</m> of which are red. Two ping pong balls are drawn without replacement. What is the probability that at least one ping pong ball is blue? In other words, what is the probability that the first ping pong ball is blue or the second ping pong ball is blue, or both?</p>
  
<p><em>Enter your answer as a fraction. </em></p>


<!--*********************************************
            User solution input
**********************************************-->  
<p><m>P(\text{at least one blue}) = </m>
  <answer>$sol</answer>
</p>

